My Winnower,<br>
<br>
You write of times past, times of pride and ambition in my life. Your words recall times when the name &quot;Merryk the Wrathful&quot; was well known and feared. They recall times when I was a rising star in the night sky. Sadly, these times have been behind me these last few months. My wrath has been blunted and my ambition turned inward. I have been more of a burden on my Harvest family than a boon. Innorruk has punished me for these faults, slowing my advancment in His mysteries and rewards until I have almost faded away.<br>
<br>
Know now, my Harvest family, that these times of lax behavior and ambition draw to a close. Merryk T'Kal, The Wrathful has RETURNED! I have seen the depradations of the Lightblind on the sands of Southern Ro, heard tell of their rising powers in the Arena, and seen their prideful, boasting words in the Grange Itself! No more I say! NO MORE! This very week I will gain my Family Name or die in the trying! I will then unleash the Wrath that you knew of old! I will find my father's sword and use it to slay the Lightblind in droves! This I swear in Innorruk's name and on my Family Name T'Kal. This I swear by my oath to the Violent Harvest!<br>
<br>
Ware Lightblind, for Merryk T'Kal comes for you! Rejoice Chosen of Innorruk for your brother has returned!<br>
<br>
I Have Spoken!<br>
<br>
Merryk T'Kal  <br>
